
On Unix:
 * install premake4 (http://industriousone.com/premake/download)
 * execute premake.sh to generate platform specific makefile
 * dependent on your platform this will tell you to either use config=release32 or config=release64
 * build unibot via 'make config=release$YOUR_ARCH' or 'gmake config=release$YOUR_ARCH' (gnu make is required)

On Windows:
 * install premake4 (http://industriousone.com/premake/download)
 * execute premake.bat to generate visual studio project files
 * open project file and build
